paper/review/sol/methodology.log-2052-   624	
paper/review/sol/methodology.log-2053-   625	8 Conclusion
paper/review/sol/methodology.log-2054-   626	Measured in health, MacKenzie Scott’s $26 billion buys a median of about 202,000 qualityadjusted life-years — several times its cost at the government’s own valuation — and most of that
paper/review/sol/methodology.log:2055:   627	health comes from the twentieth of her dollars delivered in low-income countries. The number is
paper/review/sol/methodology.log-2056-   628	a model output under stated priors, not a fact, and the model’s most important output is not
paper/review/sol/methodology.log-2057-   629	the point estimate but the machinery around it: explicit evidence weights, a 45-fold stance range
paper/review/sol/methodology.log-2058-   630	that any reader can traverse, versioned corrections, and audits committed as data. Portfolio-scale
--
