paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log:474:@tbl-geo decomposes the same run by delivery geography. The table is a by-construction decomposition, not evidence of regional differences: within each cause the model prices every delivery location identically — the health routing to global anchors is its only geographic pricing — so a cause's QALYs follow its dollars across regions. Under that construction, Sub-Saharan Africa receives `{python} ssa["% of $"]` of dollars and `{python} ssa["% of QALYs"]` of estimated QALYs at `{python} ssa["$/QALY"]` per QALY; nationally-scoped U.S. giving receives `{python} usnat["% of $"]` of dollars and `{python} usnat["% of QALYs"]` of QALYs at `{python} usnat["$/QALY"]`.
