paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log-1443- ## Corrections history
paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log-1444- 
paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log:1445:-The model reached this state through eleven public revision rounds, and the trajectory is itself evidence about the method. Cross-model review rounds cut the headline from roughly 98,000 to 87,000 QALYs (dollar-vintage normalization, a life-year/QALY conversion made explicit, a re-derived frontier benchmark, one re-attributed citation). Replacing an assumed allocation with the derivation from Scott's own database cut it to roughly 70,000. A reader's correction — health dollars had been priced at U.S. anchors regardless of delivery location — tripled it to roughly 205,000, and the subsequent two-model geography audit settled it at `{python} F["median_k"]`. Every correction is documented in the repository and summarized on the public tool; none was caught by the author unaided, and all but one were caught by models or readers rather than the author.
paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log-1446-+The model reached this state through a series of public revisions — counting a revision as a committed change that moved the headline — and the trajectory is itself evidence about the method. As recorded in the repository history:
