paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log-2150-   **LOCATION:** `paper/review/rendered.txt` lines 76–80 and 700–706; `paper/index.qmd` line 311.  
paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log:2151:   **Problem:** The revision correctly changed the introduction to say the estimate is “not a lower bound on total wellbeing,” but the limitations still call it “a floor on total wellbeing.” The latter is methodologically false under strictly positive priors that exclude zero and harmful health effects, and it directly contradicts the newly revised framing.  
paper/review/sol/reproducibility.round2.log-2152-   **Fix:** Replace “a floor on total wellbeing” with “a partial health-only accounting that omits both non-health benefits and possible harms,” or equivalent language consistent with the introduction.
